For those wondering if there is a similar campaign for Israels children I asked and if not why via email and they said;

Dear Matthew,

Thank you so much for contacting UNICEF UK, we share your deep concern about children caught up in hostilities in Israel, we have and will continue to advocate for their rights.

We are extremely concerned by the latest escalation of violence we have been witnessing since 7 October. Many children have been killed or injured, and countless others have been exposed to the violence. We are calling for the immediate cessation of hostilities, and for all parties to unconditionally
protect all children from harm and afford them the special protection to which they are entitled. We are calling for the immediate and safe release of any children being held hostage in Gaza. Any children in custody of parties to the conflict should be protected and immediately and unconditionally
released. No place is safe for children while hostilities in densely populated areas continue.

UNICEF is a neutral humanitarian organization so whilst we continue to report on and advocate for the protection of all children in both Gaza and Israel, our humanitarian response is driven by the need. Before this renewed violence, one million children were in need of humanitarian aid in Gaza and the West Bank, whereas in high-income countries, such as Israel, the State itself performs the programmatic functions that UNICEF undertakes or supports in lower income countries.

There is a National Committee for UNICEF in Israel â€“ the Israeli Fund for UNICEF which was established in 2009 and works to promote and raise awareness of childrenâ€™s rights in Israel and to raise funds for UNICEFâ€™s lifesaving work across the world. You can find out more about its work here.

I hope that you can support our call to end hostilities and for all parties to unconditionally
protect children from harm.

Once again thank you for contacting UNICEF UK.

Best wishes,

Georgia
Supporter Care Advisor
